=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_Multichannel-Expansion_ex31 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 100 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 100.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: 16.9768
  harmonic_regularity: 0.7779
  pitch_clarity: 33.0562
  inharmonicity: 0.0000
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -12.5920
  resonance_freq: 495.2637

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Multichannel Expansion Example 31
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/Multichannel-Expansion.html
// Tags: Multichannel-Expansion, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 31 ---
// three channels of Pulse are mixed to one channel
{ Mix.new(  Pulse.ar([400, 501, 600], [0.5, 0.1], 0.1) ) }.play
